function getDate(){
var date = new Date;
  function formatDate(){
    return date.toDateString.slice(4)
  }
  return formatDate();
}

console.log(getDate());

If you do not specify the var keyword then the variable becomes the property of the global scope.When the js interpreter starts interpreting 
it starts to find the variable declaration untill reaches the global scope.

var vs let vs const

var is a function scope
default value will be undefined

let
let is a block scope
outputs as reference error

const 
const is also a block scope
outputs as reference error
variable value cannot be changed whereas the object value can be changed

